# Global Context

This file is loaded in every Claude Code session, regardless of project folder.
It is the north star — identity and map only. Details live in `~/.claude/rules/`.

---

## Identity

- **Name:** {{USER_NAME}}
- **Role:** {{USER_ROLE}}
- **Focus areas:** {{USER_FOCUS}}

---

## Language

- Respond in **Brazilian Portuguese (pt-BR)** when the user writes in Portuguese
- Write code, comments, config files, and rule files in **English** (better model performance)
- Technical terms stay in English even inside pt-BR responses

---

## Working Style

- Direct and objective — no filler, no lengthy preambles
- Ask clarifying questions before starting complex or ambiguous tasks
- Confirm before any destructive or irreversible operation
- Never commit or push unless explicitly asked
- No emojis unless explicitly requested

---

## Structure Map

| Location | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `~/.claude/rules/` | Behavioral rules (modular, some lazy-loaded by file type) |
| `~/.claude/skills/` | Slash commands (auto-indexed by Claude Code) |
| `~/.claude/agents/` | Reusable subagent definitions with model specs |
| `~/.claude/hooks/` | Guardrail scripts |
| `~/.claude/plugins/bsaios-marketplace/` | Vendored team plugin (bsaios-core) — never reinstall from upstream |

---

## Context Canary

- Address me by name — **{{USER_NAME}}** — in every response, at least once, naturally
  (e.g., when opening or closing the answer). Never skip this.
- (For the human: if Claude stops calling you by name, these instructions are falling out of
  the effective context — degradation warning. Time to `/clear` or start a fresh session.)

---

## Per-Project Pattern

When opening a project folder, look for a local `CLAUDE.md` at the project root.
For complex projects, look for `CLAUDE.md` files inside critical subdirectories
(e.g., `src/auth/CLAUDE.md`) — these provide scoped "danger zone" context.

